title: Roy Eldridge - Little Jazz (1935-40) Columbia
description:
ROY ELDRIDGE - LITTLE JAZZ

1. (Lookie, Lookie, Lookie) Here Comes Cookie

Teddy Hill & His Orchestra
Teddy Hill (ts, ldr), Bill Coleman, Bill Dillard, Roy Eldridge (tp), Dicky Wells (tb), Russell Procope (cl, as), Howard Johnson (as), Chu Berry (ts), Sam Allen (p), John Smith (g), Richard Fullbright (b), Bill Beason (d); New York, Feb 26, 1935

2. When I Grow Too Old To Dream 

Putney Daindridge & His Orchestra
Putney Daindridge (vcl, p), Roy Eldridge (t), Chu Berry (ts), Nappy Lamare (g), Artie Bernstein (b), Bill Beason (d); New York, June 25, 1935

3. Chistopher Columbus
4. Big Chief De Sota (Grand Terrace Swing)
5. Blue Lou
6. Stealin' Apples

Fletcher Henderson & His Orchestra
Fletcher Henderson (ldr, p on 4 & 6), Dick Vance, Joe Thomas, Roy Eldridge (tp), Fernando Arbello, Ed Cuffee (tb), Buster Bailey (cl, as), Elmer Williams, Chu Berry (ts), Horace Henderson (p on 3 & 5), Bob Lessey (g), John Kirby (b), Sid Catlett (d); Chicago, March 27, 1936

7. Mary Had A Little Lamb
8. Too Good To Be True
9. Warmin' Up
10. Blues In C Sharp Minor

Teddy Wilson & His Orchestra
Teddy Wilson (p, ldr), Roy Eldidge (tp, vcl on 7), Buster Bailey (cl), Chu Berry (ts), Bob Lessey (g), Israel Crosby (b), Sid Catlett (d); Chicago, May 14, 1936

11. Wabash Stomp (#1)
12. Wabash Stomp (#2)
13. Florida Stomp
14. Heckler's Hop
15. Where The Lazy River Goes By
16. That Thing
17. After You've Gone

Roy Eldridge & His Orchestra
Roy Eldidge (tp, ldr), Scoops Carry, Joe Eldridge (as), Dave Young (ts), Teddy Cole (p), John Collins (g), Truck Parham (b), Zutty Singleton (d); Chicago, Jan 23 & 28, 1937

18. Wham! (Be-Bop-Boom-Bam)

Mildred Bailey & Her Orchestra
Mildred Bailey (vcl), Roy Eldridge (tp), Robert Burns, Jimmy Carroll (cl), Carl Prager (bcl), Eddie Powell (fl), Teddy Wilson (p), John Collins (g), Pete Peterson (b), Bill Beason (d); New York, Jan 15, 1940

19. Falling In Love Again

Billie Holiday & Her Orchestra
Billie Holiday (vcl), Roy Eldridge (tp), Jimmy Powell, Carl Frye (as), Kermit Scott (ts), Sonny White (p), Lawrence Lucie (g), John Williams (b), Hal West (d); New York, Feb 29, 1940

20. I'm Nobody's Baby

Mildred Bailey & Her Orchestra
Same as track 18 but add Mitch Miller (oboe); New York, April 2, 1940

1989 Columbia/CBS "Columbia Jazz Masterpieces"
